---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
    title="tcplot(Data Visualization Twin Cities)"
    description="tcplot() — a Twin Cities community for data visualization practitioners, enthusiasts, and storytellers."
    image="/images/tcplot(colorswithtext).png"
>
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-8">
        <!-- Header -->
        <div class="text-center mb-12">
            <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">
                tcplot(&#x1F3A8;&#x1F4BB;&#x1F3A4;)
            </h1>
            <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 max-w-3xl mx-auto leading-relaxed">
                tcplot() is a Twin Cities community for data visualization
                practitioners, enthusiasts, and storytellers. Whether you are a
                D3 wizard, a Tableau pro, a ggplot2 devotee, or someone who
                appreciates a well-crafted chart, you've found your people.
            </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Colors Image -->
        <div class="flex justify-center mb-12">
            <div class="max-w-2xl w-full rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
                <img
                    src="/images/tcplot(colorswithtext).png"
                    alt="tcplot() data visualization twin cities — colorful mosaic collage of rectangular chart elements"
                    class="w-full h-auto object-contain"
                />
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- About Section -->
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto mb-12">
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
                Our mission is to elevate the data literacy and design standards
                of the MSP area through three core pillars:
            </p>
            <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-600 mb-6">
                <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                    <span class="mt-1 text-gray-400">&#x25B8;</span>
                    <span
                        ><strong class="text-gray-900">Talks:</strong> Hear from local
                        experts and industry leaders on the "why" and "how" of great
                        visualization.</span
                    >
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                    <span class="mt-1 text-gray-400">&#x25B8;</span>
                    <span
                        ><strong class="text-gray-900">Workshops:</strong> Roll up
                        your sleeves for hands-on sessions where we master new tools,
                        libraries, and design principles.</span
                    >
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                    <span class="mt-1 text-gray-400">&#x25B8;</span>
                    <span
                        ><strong class="text-gray-900">Build-a-thons:</strong> Join
                        collaborative coworking where we take datasets and turn them
                        into impactful, interactive, or artistic visual stories.</span
                    >
                </li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Links -->
        <div class="flex justify-center gap-6 mt-12">
            <a
                href="https://www.instagram.com/tcplot/"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                class="text-blue-600 hover:underline font-medium"
            >
                Instagram
            </a>
            <a
                href="https://www.meetup.com/tcplot/?eventOrigin=home_groups_you_organize"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                class="text-blue-600 hover:underline font-medium"
            >
                Meetup
            </a>
        </div>

        <!-- Event: Claude Code Workshop -->
        <div
            id="claude-code"
            class="max-w-4xl mx-auto mt-16 mb-12 scroll-mt-20"
        >
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">
                Upcoming: Claude Code for Data Visualization — May 23rd
            </h2>

            <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
                AI-assisted coding is changing how visualization practitioners
                prototype, iterate, and ship. In this hands-on workshop, we'll
                get you up and running with Claude Code — Anthropic's agentic
                coding tool — and put it to work on real dataviz problems. No
                prior experience with AI coding tools required.
            </p>
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
                Whether you're deep in D3, grinding through ggplot2, or
                somewhere in between, you'll leave with a working setup and a
                concrete sense of where Claude Code fits (and doesn't fit) in a
                practitioner's workflow.
            </p>

            <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">
                Location & Logistics
            </h3>
            <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-600">
                <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                    <span class="mt-1 text-gray-400">&#x25B8;</span>
                    <span
                        ><strong class="text-gray-900">When:</strong> Saturday, May
                        23 · 10:00 AM to 12:00 PM CDT</span
                    >
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                    <span class="mt-1 text-gray-400">&#x25B8;</span>
                    <span
                        ><strong class="text-gray-900">Where:</strong> The Coffee
                        Shop NE, 2852 Johnson St NE, Minneapolis, MN</span
                    >
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                    <span class="mt-1 text-gray-400">&#x25B8;</span>
                    <span>Make sure to bring your laptop and charger.</span>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Event: Data Physicalization Workshop -->
        <div
            id="data-physicalization"
            class="max-w-4xl mx-auto mt-16 mb-12 scroll-mt-20"
        >
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">
                Upcoming: Data Physicalization Workshop — June 27th
            </h2>

            <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4 italic">
                What if your next chart wasn't on a screen?
            </p>
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
                Join tcplot() for a hands-on morning of data physicalization —
                translating real datasets into objects you can hold, turn over,
                and put on your desk. We'll explore paper, thread, beads, and
                the surprisingly hard question of what to encode when you can't
                reach for a library.
            </p>
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
                We'll draw inspiration from projects like Giorgia Lupi and
                Stefanie Posavec's <em>Dear Data</em>, Nathalie Miebach's
                weather sculptures, and the broader tradition of data
                physicalization (<a
                    href="https://dataphys.org"
                    target="_blank"
                    rel="noopener noreferrer"
                    class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">dataphys.org</a
                >). The constraint is the point: when you can't pipe data into
                ggplot, you have to make real decisions about hierarchy,
                encoding, and what's actually worth showing.
            </p>

            <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">
                What you'll do
            </h3>
            <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-600 mb-6">
                <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                    <span class="mt-1 text-gray-400">&#x25B8;</span>
                    <span
                        >Pick from a handful of small, pre-prepared datasets (<a
                            href="https://www.dnr.state.mn.us/climate/historical/daily.html"
                            target="_blank"
                            rel="noopener noreferrer"
                            class="text-blue-600 hover:underline"
                            >Twin Cities weather</a
                        >, <a
                            href="https://science.ebird.org/en/use-ebird-data/download-ebird-data-products"
                            target="_blank"
                            rel="noopener noreferrer"
                            class="text-blue-600 hover:underline"
                            >MN bird sightings</a
                        >, <a
                            href="https://opendata.minneapolismn.gov/"
                            target="_blank"
                            rel="noopener noreferrer"
                            class="text-blue-600 hover:underline"
                            >library checkouts</a
                        >, a week of your own personal data, or any other data)</span
                    >
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                    <span class="mt-1 text-gray-400">&#x25B8;</span>
                    <span
                        >Work solo or in pairs to translate it into a physical
                        artifact</span
                    >
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                    <span class="mt-1 text-gray-400">&#x25B8;</span>
                    <span>Share what you made and what surprised you</span>
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                    <span class="mt-1 text-gray-400">&#x25B8;</span>
                    <span>Leave with the object you built</span>
                </li>
            </ul>

            <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">
                What we'll provide
            </h3>
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
                Cardstock, embroidery thread, beads, tape, markers, making
                supplies, datasets printed and ready to go.
            </p>

            <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">
                What to bring
            </h3>
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
                Yourself. Optionally, a week of personal data you've been
                tracking (sleep, coffee, steps, moods, anything) or your own
                craft supplies of choice.
            </p>

            <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">
                Who this is for
            </h3>
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
                Anyone curious about data visualization — practitioners working
                in D3, Tableau, ggplot2, Observable, or none of the above. No
                craft skills required.
            </p>

            <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
                Hope to see you there!
            </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Event: API Build-a-thon -->
        <div
            id="api-build-a-thon"
            class="max-w-4xl mx-auto mt-16 mb-12 scroll-mt-20"
        >
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">
                Past Event: An API Build-a-thon on April 4th
            </h2>

            <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
                Are you ready to build a digital masterpiece? Whether you want
                to curate a virtual gallery using The Met, track near-earth
                objects with NASA, or dive into the digital archives of the
                Natural History Museum, this is your playground.
            </p>
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
                There's no set prompt—only a treasure trove of world-class APIs
                and a room full of creative minds. You pick the data, you pick
                the stack, and create your own adventure.
            </p>

            <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">
                The Mission
            </h3>
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
                You have one day to build a project using at least one culture,
                science, or other cool API. We'll provide a curated list of fun
                APIs to get your gears turning, but the final destination is up
                to you.
            </p>

            <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">
                Potential Quests
            </h3>
            <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-600 mb-8">
                <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                    <span class="mt-1 text-gray-400">&#x25B8;</span>
                    <span
                        ><strong class="text-gray-900">The Curator:</strong> Build
                        a "Daily Masterpiece" bot using <a
                            href="https://metmuseum.github.io/"
                            target="_blank"
                            rel="noopener noreferrer"
                            class="text-blue-600 hover:underline"
                            >The Metropolitan Museum of Art API</a
                        >.</span
                    >
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                    <span class="mt-1 text-gray-400">&#x25B8;</span>
                    <span
                        ><strong class="text-gray-900">The Astronaut:</strong> Create
                        a live asteroid tracker or a Mars Rover gallery using <a
                            href="https://api.nasa.gov/"
                            target="_blank"
                            rel="noopener noreferrer"
                            class="text-blue-600 hover:underline"
                            >NASA Open APIs</a
                        >.</span
                    >
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                    <span class="mt-1 text-gray-400">&#x25B8;</span>
                    <span
                        ><strong class="text-gray-900">The Explorer:</strong> Map
                        out biodiversity hotspots using the <a
                            href="https://www.gbif.org/developer/summary"
                            target="_blank"
                            rel="noopener noreferrer"
                            class="text-blue-600 hover:underline"
                            >Global Biodiversity Information Facility (GBIF)</a
                        >.</span
                    >
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                    <span class="mt-1 text-gray-400">&#x25B8;</span>
                    <span
                        ><strong class="text-gray-900">The Historian:</strong> Connect
                        the dots of the past using the <a
                            href="https://www.si.edu/openaccess"
                            target="_blank"
                            rel="noopener noreferrer"
                            class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Smithsonian</a
                        > or <a
                            href="https://www.loc.gov/apis/"
                            target="_blank"
                            rel="noopener noreferrer"
                            class="text-blue-600 hover:underline"
                            >Library of Congress</a
                        > data.</span
                    >
                </li>
            </ul>

            <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">
                More Cool APIs
            </h3>
            <div
                class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-x-8 gap-y-2 text-gray-600 mb-8"
            >
                <div>
                    <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-3 mb-2">
                        Science & Nature
                    </h4>
                    <ul class="space-y-1">
                        <li>
                            &#x25B8; <a
                                href="https://api.nasa.gov/"
                                target="_blank"
                                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                                class="text-blue-600 hover:underline"
                                >NASA APIs</a
                            > — APOD, Mars rovers, asteroids
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            &#x25B8; <a
                                href="https://www.gbif.org/developer/summary"
                                target="_blank"
                                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                                class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">GBIF</a
                            > — Global biodiversity data
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            &#x25B8; <a
                                href="https://openweathermap.org/api"
                                target="_blank"
                                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                                class="text-blue-600 hover:underline"
                                >OpenWeatherMap</a
                            > — Weather data
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            &#x25B8; <a
                                href="https://earthquake.usgs.gov/fdsnws/event/1/"
                                target="_blank"
                                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                                class="text-blue-600 hover:underline"
                                >USGS Earthquake API</a
                            > — Real-time quake data
                        </li>
                    </ul>

                    <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-3 mb-2">
                        Health & Public Data
                    </h4>
                    <ul class="space-y-1">
                        <li>
                            &#x25B8; <a
                                href="https://www.who.int/data/gho/info/gho-odata-api"
                                target="_blank"
                                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                                class="text-blue-600 hover:underline"
                                >WHO GHO API</a
                            > — Global health data
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            &#x25B8; <a
                                href="https://wonder.cdc.gov/"
                                target="_blank"
                                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                                class="text-blue-600 hover:underline"
                                >CDC WONDER</a
                            > — Public health datasets
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            &#x25B8; <a
                                href="https://open.fda.gov/apis/"
                                target="_blank"
                                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                                class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">OpenFDA</a
                            > — Drug events, recalls, labeling
                        </li>
                    </ul>

                    <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-3 mb-2">
                        Space & Astronomy
                    </h4>
                    <ul class="space-y-1">
                        <li>
                            &#x25B8; <a
                                href="https://github.com/r-spacex/SpaceX-API"
                                target="_blank"
                                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                                class="text-blue-600 hover:underline"
                                >SpaceX API</a
                            > — Launches, rockets, capsules
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            &#x25B8; <a
                                href="http://open-notify.org/Open-Notify-API/"
                                target="_blank"
                                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                                class="text-blue-600 hover:underline"
                                >Open Notify</a
                            > — ISS location, astronauts in space
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-3 mb-2">
                        Culture & Fun
                    </h4>
                    <ul class="space-y-1">
                        <li>
                            &#x25B8; <a
                                href="https://data.rijksmuseum.nl/docs/"
                                target="_blank"
                                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                                class="text-blue-600 hover:underline"
                                >Rijksmuseum API</a
                            > — Art collection data
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            &#x25B8; <a
                                href="https://openlibrary.org/developers/api"
                                target="_blank"
                                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                                class="text-blue-600 hover:underline"
                                >Open Library API</a
                            > — Book metadata
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            &#x25B8; <a
                                href="https://pokeapi.co/docs/v2"
                                target="_blank"
                                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                                class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">PokeAPI</a
                            > — Pokemon data
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            &#x25B8; <a
                                href="https://developer.themoviedb.org/docs/getting-started"
                                target="_blank"
                                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                                class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">TMDB</a
                            > — Film and TV data
                        </li>
                    </ul>

                    <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-3 mb-2">
                        Geospatial & Environment
                    </h4>
                    <ul class="space-y-1">
                        <li>
                            &#x25B8; <a
                                href="https://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Overpass_API"
                                target="_blank"
                                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                                class="text-blue-600 hover:underline"
                                >OpenStreetMap</a
                            > — Map & geographic data
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            &#x25B8; <a
                                href="https://www.globalforestwatch.org/help/developers/"
                                target="_blank"
                                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                                class="text-blue-600 hover:underline"
                                >Global Forest Watch</a
                            > — Deforestation data
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            &#x25B8; <a
                                href="https://www.ncdc.noaa.gov/cdo-web/webservices/v2"
                                target="_blank"
                                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                                class="text-blue-600 hover:underline"
                                >NOAA Climate Data</a
                            > — Historical weather records
                        </li>
                    </ul>

                    <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-3 mb-2">
                        Economics & Society
                    </h4>
                    <ul class="space-y-1">
                        <li>
                            &#x25B8; <a
                                href="https://datahelpdesk.worldbank.org/knowledgebase/articles/889392-about-the-indicators-api-documentation"
                                target="_blank"
                                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                                class="text-blue-600 hover:underline"
                                >World Bank API</a
                            > — Development indicators
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            &#x25B8; <a
                                href="https://www.census.gov/data/developers.html"
                                target="_blank"
                                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                                class="text-blue-600 hover:underline"
                                >Census Bureau API</a
                            > — US demographic data
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            &#x25B8; <a
                                href="https://fred.stlouisfed.org/docs/api/fred/"
                                target="_blank"
                                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                                class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">FRED</a
                            > — Economic time series data
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

            <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">
                Location & Logistics
            </h3>
            <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-600">
                <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                    <span class="mt-1 text-gray-400">&#x25B8;</span>
                    <span>Make sure to bring your laptop and charger.</span>
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                    <span class="mt-1 text-gray-400">&#x25B8;</span>
                    <span
                        ><strong class="text-gray-900">Where:</strong> The Coffee
                        Shop NE, 2852 Johnson St NE, Minneapolis, MN 55418</span
                    >
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                    <span class="mt-1 text-gray-400">&#x25B8;</span>
                    <span
                        ><strong class="text-gray-900">When:</strong> 12PM on April
                        4th</span
                    >
                </li>
            </ul>
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mt-6">
                Why join? Because the world's most interesting data is sitting
                behind an API key, waiting for someone to do something awesome
                with it. Why not you?
            </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Petri Image -->
        <div class="flex justify-center mt-12">
            <div class="max-w-2xl w-full rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
                <img
                    src="/images/tcplot(petriwithtext).png"
                    alt="tcplot() data visualization twin cities — collage featuring a scientist with a petri dish, eclipse, and time series chart"
                    class="w-full h-auto object-contain"
                />
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</Layout>
